post_text:
Good morning!
If you are having technical issues with virtual learning, please do the following.

Please send an email to support@iaf-sabis.net with the following information. We have a support person who is dedicated to responding to this email each day.

1. Parent's full name
2. Student's full name
3. What do you need? A password reset for your Chrome book? A password reset for Microsoft Teams? Please be specific what the password information is for.

4. If you are having trouble with your device or not sure how to even log-in, please bring the device with you to IAF between the hours of 7:30 - 4:00. We will assist you to make sure that your child can get on.

5. If you have a question different from above, please private message us via Facebook and we will do our best to assist you.

Thank you for your patience. We are working daily to assist you.

FAMILIES -- Important update regarding MTA and ridership for this fall. Deadline is this Thursday, August 13.

Any student participating in "in-person"learning and planning to use MTA transportation, MUST submit a Transportation Request form in order to ride the bus.

Families have until Thursday, August 13, 2020, to submit the request which is included below. If you filled out the survey stating a request for MTA transportation you do not need to submit another request. Parents/Guardians can contact Mrs. Giles @ (810)600-5264 or kgiles@sabis.net to submit their request. Anyone riding the bus is required to wear a face mask or covering. A letter from MTA was distributed previously and available on IAF's website at https://iaf.sabis.net.

post_text: Please view and share the positivity! Also please feel free to like and follow International Academy of Flint 100 Students 100 Stories Positivity Project
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
IAF Positivity Project: Angelina Imagine by John Lennon

International Academy of Flint 100 Students 100 Stories Positivity Project
June 24 at 2:07 PM ·

Hello again, everyone! Hope you're having a wonderful Wednesday. The Student Life Organization @ International Academy of Flint is back with another story in our 100 Stories Positivity Project. We welcome you to sit back and relax to enjoy this story.

Today's story is read by Angelina, and is a short story version of the song "Imagine," by John Lennon, a song which you might have been hearing a lot about recently. We hope this lovely story will bring some more positivity in your life, as with the rest of our stories.

We hope you enjoy this awesome story! If you do enjoy, make sure to share this video with a friend or family member. And make sure to check out the rest of the videos uploaded to the channel, there's a good bit of them now. Anyways, we hope to see you again tomorrow with our next video! Have a great day!

#IAF #internationalacademyofflint #youthservice #100students100stories #GYSD2020 #GYSDMI #IAFyouthproject #IAFpositivityproject

post_text:
The day has come! Seniors, today is YOUR day, and even though this day looks completely different than any of us envisioned for you, we have some good news! We do still have to follow the COVID-19 plan that was mailed and email to you all last week, but with that being said we can now allow you to bring chairs and sit outside of your car given the Stay at Home order was lifted. Please stay with only those that you came with and still practice social distancing. We are excited to see you all tonight and the weather is beautiful!

One last thing Seniors- you MUST turn in your textbooks and Chromebooks or we have to hold your diploma until those are returned. If you have any questions please email Ms. Vincent at mvincent@sabis.net

See you all tonight :)

post_text:
Senior Families-
You should have received a paper copy of the routes that we mailed home to Seniors last Friday. Here is a digital copy you can share with loved ones so we can fill the route from IAF to FIA with as many people as possible to cheer our Seniors on! Please note, that only one car per Senior is allowed in the first parking lot at FIA. We will have parking monitors there so they will be able to direct you and others that decide to join us on where to park.

Please expect to receive an email and letter mailed home regarding our COVID-19 plan. We HAVE to have a copy of this plan signed by each Senior parent. Once emailed out or you receive in the mail, you can print out, sign and take a picture of it and email it back to us at iaf@sabis.net or send us a picture of it on FB Messenger.

If we do not receive one by Thursday morning, expect to have someone get you to sign this at IAF while setting up for the parade.

Thank you- IAF

post_text:
The Genesee Opportunity (GO) stipend provides Genesee County high school graduates with money for college, career training, or certification licensing fees. To be eligible, you must reside in Genesee County, Michigan or on a property that is taxed by a Genesee County school district and be a graduate, from a high school in Genesee County. Graduates must be enrolled in an eligible training program or post-secondary educational institution and submit an application by the due date. The GO stipend can only be awarded one time and must be used within the first 12 months after graduation or GED completion.
The GO stipend is not based on income or grades, and is funded through a millage approved by Genesee County voters.
Important! All 2020 graduates who wish to use the GO Stipend must submit the application form. 2020 graduates must apply by May 15, 2020.

https://geneseego.org/home/application

Hello Parents/Guardians:

One of the ways we are trying to provide materials to students is via the SABIS® Digital Platform (Web School).

The SABIS® Digital Platform can be accessed by going to the following site via your web browser: https://digitalplatform.sabis.net or download the app.

We have uploaded packets of documents, in Adobe PDF format, per grade level. You will see a message at the top left of the screen after you have logged in under announcements. If you click on the message, you will be taken to a screen in which you can download the documents.

If you are not able to login to the SABIS® Digital Platform, please email tdaggett@sabis.net, including your name, your student(s) name(s), and grade levels and I will send your credentials to login via email.

Tony Daggett
Regional IT Manager - Michigan

post_text: Vacation is very near— one more day! This is a reminder that we have a full day of school tomorrow and we have exams in the morning. Busses run normal time with dismissal at 3:30. There is an optional half day of dismissal at 12:30 with a signed permission slip. If a student doesn’t come tomorrow we will be requesting students to come in over Winter Break to complete missing final exams so we can finalize report cards that will go home in early January. Thank you!

post_text:
URGENT: New Bills introduced to restore charter funding and we need you to be heard in order to help!

It has been over 2 months since funding was cut for charter schools across Michigan and this means IAF!. Charter schools will soon be missing their third State Aid payment without the additional funding. We believe there is a chance to restore this funding over the next couple of weeks and we need your help!

School funding must put the needs of our children first, not the interests of politicians and bureaucracy! We are only asking that we get the same funding as all other public schools.

Please --- Clink the link below and act now. Thank you!

https://www.votervoice.net/MICHARTERS/campaigns/69716/respond
shared_text:
VOTERVOICE.NET
Please support SB 555 and HB 5077!
